('RUSSIAN STUDIES GUEST SPEAKER SPRING LECTURE SERIES: IMAGES OF RUPTURE IN CIVILIZATION BETWEEN EAST ', 'Lectures, Seminars', '17.00 - 19.00', '2015-03-08', 'Screening and open discussion \r\n\r\nBased on a short masterpiece by Vasily Grossman, "In the Town of Berdichev," the film was banned in the Soviet Union due to its controversial treatment of Holocaust. Director Askoldov lost his job and was expelled from Moscow. He was told that the single copy of the film had been destroyed. The film was reconstructed and finally released in 1988, winning the Special Jury Prize at the Berlin International Film Festival. Film music by Alfred SCHNITTKE (1934-1998).\r\n\r\nCost\r\nFree', 'Scotiabank Auditorium, McCain Building', 37),
('PHD DEFENCE - DEPARTMENT OF INDUSTRIAL ENGINEERING', 'Lectures, Seminars', '10.30 ', '2015-03-09', 'The Faculty of Graduate Studies wishes to announce Navin Chari, PhD candidate from the Department of Industrial engineering, will be defending his thesis entitled "Thematic Development of Recovery, Remanufacturing, and Support Models for Sustainable Supply Chains" on Monday, March 9th at 10:30 a.m.\r\n\r\nCost: Free', 'Room 3107, The Mona Campbell Building, 1459 LeMarchant Street', 38),
