('RUSSIAN STUDIES GUEST SPEAKER SPRING LECTURE SERIES: IMAGES OF RUPTURE IN CIVILIZATION BETWEEN EAST ', 'Lectures, Seminars', '18.00 - 19.00', '2015-03-10', '"Images of Rupture in Civilization Between East and West: The Perception of Auschwita and Hiroshima in Eastern European Arts and Media" \r\nProfessor Urs Heftrich \r\n(Director of Slavic Institute, University of Heidelberg, Germany)\r\n\r\nAdditional Information\r\nAll events are open to the general public and free of charge.\r\n\r\nContact\r\nContact the organizer of the Guest Speaker Lecture Spring Series: Prof. Yuri Leving, 902-494-3473, yleving@dal.ca. \r\n\r\nProudly sponsored by The Atlantic Jewish Council (AJC).', 'Room 1116, McCain Building', 43),
('AUTHOR READING WITH DR. JAMES RAFFAN', 'Lectures, Seminars', '19.30', '2015-03-10', 'Best-selling author Dr. James Raffan will be doing a public reading at 7:30 p.m. on Tuesday, Mar. 10 at the Killam Memorial Library. \r\n\r\nDr. Raffan will be reading from his latest book. Circling the Midnight Sun: Culture and Change in the Invisible Arctic, which was a finalist for the 2015 BC National Non-Fiction Book Prize and named a “best book” of 2014 by the Globe and Mail \r\n\r\nJames is a prolific writer, speaker, geographer and Kickass Canadian (kickasscanadians.ca/james-raffan) who has produced a number of bestselling books. \r\n\r\nHe has also written for media outlets including Canadian Geographic, National Geographic, Explore, The Globe and Mail, as well as for CBC Radio and The Discovery Channel. \r\n\r\nThis public reading is sponsored by the Canadian Literary Collections Project.', 'Archives & Special Collections Reading Room, Fifth Floor, Killam Library', 44),
