('PHD DEFENCE - FACULTY OF COMPUTER SCIENCE', 'Lectures, Seminars', '9.30', '2015-03-11', 'The Faculty of Graduate Studies wishes to announce Naureen Nizam, PhD candidate from the Faculty of Computer Science, will be defending her thesis entitled "Using Social Media Data to Improve Navigation within Websites" on Wednesday, March 11th at 9:00 a.m.\r\n\r\nCost\r\nFree\r\n', 'Room 403, The Goldberg Computer Science Building', 46),
('PARENT DISCUSSION OF ANOREXIA NERVOSA', 'Health and Wellness', '12.15 - 13.15', '2015-03-11', 'Anorexia Nervosa is an insidious brain-based disease that will strike long before you as a parent will know it’s happening. One in ten people who develop anorexia will die from it, and it’s on the rise in Nova Scotia, but early intervention is the key to full recovery. \r\n\r\nAs a parent of a daughter who has recovered from anorexia, your presenter wants to tell you what she wishes she had known when her daughter was three years old because that’s how early you can take action to prevent this horrific disease from manifesting. \r\n\r\nIn this hour-long session we will look at the signs and symptoms, risk factors and causes, many of which will surprise and even shock you. And most importantly we will look at ways to mitigate risks and recognize the earliest signs. \r\n\r\nCost\r\nFree\r\n', 'Room B400, lower level, Killam Library', 47),
('PARLIAMENTARISM IN CRISIS: THE IMPACT OF THE EUROZONE CRISIS ON THE LEGITIMACY AND AUTONOMY OF THE GREEK PARLIAMENT', 'Lectures, Seminars', '12.30 - 14.30', '2015-03-11', 'Political scientists started recently examining the political aspects of the Greek economic crisis, but a crucial dimension has remained unexplored: the impact on the legitimacy and powers of the Greek parliament. This talk discusses the wounded autonomy of the Greek parliament and its rapid deligitmation as a consequence of the European economic crisis. Despite these problems, hardly any steps have been taken so far to reform the parliament and restore public trust. As a result, the Greek parliament remains hostage to volatile utilitarian support resting on the country’s economic performance. Given that the country’s economic future is more precarious than ever, the prospects for parliamentary democracy in Greece appear bleak.\r\n\r\nCost\r\nFree', 'Lord Dalhousie Room, Henry Hicks Bldg', 48),
