('GLOBAL HEALTH TOWN HALL', 'Special Events', '17.30 - 19.30', '2015-03-31', 'Dalhousie`s Global Health Office invites you to this special global health event. \r\n\r\nWhat is Global Health @ Dalhousie? \r\n\r\nShawna O’Hearn, Director of the Global Health Office, will discuss the future of global health in our community. \r\n\r\nGuest Speaker: Dr. Rohit Ramchandani \r\n\r\nPublic health adviser & principal investigator, ColaLife; Founder & Executive Director, Antara Global Health Advisors; Doctor of Public Health Candidate, Johns Hopkins School of Public Health; Adjunct Lecturer, University of Waterloo School of Public Health & Health Systems. Recognized as a “Rising Star in Global Health”, Rohit played a key role in guiding the development of ColaLife, establishing new partnerships, and writing concept papers. His work focuses on improving lives, increasing equity, and preventing needless loss of life by providing global health expertise, experience, partnerships, and evidence-based public health and management advice. \r\n\r\nThe event will also celebrate Global Health Awards, Photo Contest and the graduation ceremony. \r\n\r\nGraduations: \r\nAdvocates in Global Health \r\nHealth Systems Certificate \r\n\r\nAwards: \r\nDr. Ron Stewart Student Award \r\nDr. Jock Murray Resident Award \r\nDr. John Savage Memorial Faculty Award', 'Halifax: Tupper Th. A; Saint John: DMNB rm 105', 95),
('FOUNTAIN SCHOOL OF PERFORMING ARTS STAGE PRODUCTION: THE SEAGULL', 'Concerts, Performances & Arts', '20.00', '2015-03-31', 'By Anton Chekhov \r\nIn a version by Martin Crimp \r\nDirected by Tanja Jacobs \r\nSir James Dunn Theatre \r\n“I’m a seagull… \r\nNo, that’s not it. I’m \r\nan actress.” \r\nTo the bored inhabitants of a stifling country estate, seagulls seem happy and free—and so does the stage. Clever, innocent Nina dreams of becoming an actress, and the young playwright Konstantin is determined to reinvent theatre. But they are surrounded by the disappointed, the cynical and the unimaginative. Can artistic and romantic dreams come true in a world where flight can be halted by the hunter’s gun?\r\n\r\nLocation\r\nSir James Dunn Theatre, Dalhousie Arts Centre, 6101 University Avenue\r\nCost\r\n$15 / $10 for individual tickets or purchase a 5-concert package and save!\r\nAdditional Information\r\nAll shows at 8:00 pm. with an additional 2 pm matinee on the Saturday.\r\n\r\nContact\r\nTickets available at the Dalhousie Arts Centre Box Office. Tel 902.494.3820 or 1.800.874.1669 or dal.ca/artscentre', 'Sir James Dunn Theatre, Dalhousie Arts Centre, 6101 University Avenue', 96),
('FOUNTAIN SCHOOL OF PERFORMING ARTS SPRING GALA', 'Concerts, Performances & Arts', '19.30', '2015-04-07', 'In celebration of the Fountain School’s inaugural season, we conclude the academic year with a gala concert featuring the Dalhousie Chorus, Chamber Orchestra, and Symphony Orchestra together on the stage of the Rebecca Cohn Auditorium, conducted by Christina Murray, Philippe Djokic and Peter Oleskevich. The program will include a selection of great opera choruses.\r\n\r\nCost\r\n$20 / $15 Available at the Dalhousie Arts Centre Box Office\r\nAdditional Information\r\nTickets available at the Dalhousie Arts Centre Box Office: 902.494.3820, 1.800.494.3820, dal.ca/artscentre', 'Rebecca Cohn Auditorium, 6101 University Ave', 97),
