('EBOOK DAYS @ DAL', 'Training & Professional Development', '9.00 AM', '2015-03-17', 'Did you know that the Dalhousie Libraries provide access to over 400,000 electronic books, in every subject area?\r\n\r\nEbooks offer many great features you may not be aware of. Join us for a day of discussion and information sharing at “eBook Days at Dal,” a special event hosted by the Dalhousie Libraries in partnership with publishers Elsevier, Proquest and Springer. Publisher reps will be on hand to answer your questions and give out cool freebies.\r\n\r\nWhen: Tuesday March 17 and Wednesday, March 18\r\n\r\nEvent Schedule:\r\n\r\nMacRae Library\r\nTuesday, March 17\r\n9 – 11 a.m. Meet and greet with representatives from Elsevier and Springer\r\n\r\nSexton Library\r\nTuesday, March 17\r\n2 – 4 p.m. Meet and greet with representatives from Elsevier and Springer\r\n\r\nKellogg Library\r\nWednesday, March 18\r\n9 – 11 a.m. Meet and greet with representatives from Proquest, Elsevier and Springer (Tupper Link)\r\n\r\nKillam Library\r\nWednesday, March 18\r\n12 – 1:30 p.m. Author Workshop with Springer and Elsevier * (G70)\r\n* Geared toward future authors as well as those interested in learning about available author tools, these workshops will offer advice from the experts, with an opportunity for discussion as well as Q&A.&#8206; Springer will host the first half of the workshop and Elsevier the second half.\r\n\r\n2 – 4 p.m. Meet and greet with representatives from Proquest, Elsevier and Springer (Killam Library)\r\n\r\nFill out the following survey for a chance to win a prize! https://surveys.dal.ca/opinio/s?s=27818\r\n\r\nResults from this Ebooks survey will help us make decisions about future purchases and services at Dal. The survey will be open from March 16-31.\r\n\r\nCategory\r\nTraining & Professional Development\r\n\r\nTime\r\nStarts: Tuesday March 17, 2015 - 09:00 AM \r\nEnds: Wednesday March 18, 2015 - 04:00 PM\r\n\r\nLocation\r\nKillam/Sexton/Kellogg and MacRae Libraries\r\n\r\nCost\r\nNo cost\r\n\r\nContact\r\nIf you have any questions about Ebook Days @ Dal please email kellelec@dal.ca.', 'Multiple Location', 101),
('Training & Professional Development', 'Movies & Film', '19.00 - 21.45', '2015-03-19', 'Novel Tech Ethics (Faculty of Medicine, Dalhousie University) is offering a public screening of WALTZ WITH BASHIR (2008 Oscar nominee & Golden Globe winner, Best Foreign Language Film)\r\n-    Synopsis: An Israeli film director interviews fellow veterans of the 1982 invasion of Lebanon to reconstruct his own memories of his term of service in that conflict.\r\n-    Issues to be discussed: Post-traumatic stress disorder; trauma; memory; coping & resilience.\r\n-    Panelists: Alon Friedman (Neuroscience); Kenneth Cooper (Psychiatry & Canadian Forces); TBA (Patient Rep)\r\nPlease distribute this invitation widely. All are welcome. Admission is free. Join the Facebook page for this event:\r\nor look here on the NTE website for further details: /19/waltzing_with_bashir___brain_awareness_week.htmlhttp://www.dal.ca/sites/noveltechethics/news-events/PastEvents/2015/03/19/waltzing_with_bashir___brain_awareness_week.html\r\n\r\nCategory\r\nMovies & Film\r\n\r\nTime\r\nStarts: Thursday March 19, 2015 - 07:00 PM \r\nEnds: Thursday March 19, 2015 - 09:45 PM\r\n\r\nLocation\r\nQEII Royal Bank Theatre, ground floor, Halifax Infirmary, 1796 Summer St. entrance\r\n\r\nCost\r\nFree', 'QEII Royal Bank Theatre, ground floor, Halifax Infirmary, 1796 Summer St. entrance', 102),
