('MULTI-AGENT SYSTEMS: AN APPLICATION TO MANUFACTURING', 'Lectures, Seminars', '11:30 - 12:30', '2015-04-01', 'In manufacturing environments, the control of system elements such as automated guided vehicles (AGVs) has some difficulties when planning operations dynamically. Multi agent-based systems, a newly maturing area of distributed artificial intelligence, provide some effective mechanisms for the management of such dynamic operations in manufacturing environments. The present research proposes a multi-agent based scheduling approach for AGVs and machines within a manufacturing system. The proposed multi-agent based approach works under a real-time environment and generates feasible schedules using negotiation/bidding mechanisms between agents.', 'MA310', 104),
