('SOFTWARE ENGINEERING AT FACEBOOK', 'Lectures, Seminars', '17:00', '2015-04-01', 'FCS Alumnus, Peter O''Hearn, will be here to talk about what it''s like to work at Facebook. \r\n\r\nFacebook''s company mission is to make the world more open and connected, and it does this via a collection of products which are used by over a billion people in total. \r\n\r\nBehind the products is a fast-moving engineering organization working at the edge of current technology. In this talk Peter will give you a flavour of what it is like to do engineering in a leading software company, and the kinds of skills that are relevant to this sort of work. \r\n\r\nBio \r\nPeter O''Hearn received his BSc in Computer Science form Dalhousie in 1985. After obtaining his Msc and PhD from Queen''s he spent a number of years as an academic in the US and the UK, before moving to Facebook in 2013 when his startup company, Monoidics, was acquired. Peter is currently an Engineering Manager working out of Facebook''s London office and also a Professor at University College London.', 'CIBC Auditorium, Goldberg Computer Science Building, 6050 University Avenue', 110),
