('3 MINUTE THESIS - OPEN ROUNDS', 'Special Events', 'Starts: Thursday April 9, 2015 - 10:00 A', '2015-04-09', 'The Faculty of Graduate Studies (FGS) is excited to announce the third annual Three Minute Thesis (3MT) competition at Dalhousie University. Preliminary heats will take place on Thursday April 9th. The competitions are open to the public, and faculty and staff are encouraged to support the competition both by encouraging students to compete and by coming out to watch the participants on Thursday April 9th. We would also like to invite faculty to bring classes to watch the heats on April 9th.', 'University Hall, Macdonald Building, 6300 Coburg Road', 123),
('AFRO-CUBAN JAZZ AND BEYOND WITH IGNACIO BERROA AND HILARIO DURAN', 'Concerts, Performances & Arts', 'April 7, 2015 - 11:30 AM - April 9, 2015', '2015-04-09', 'AFRO-CUBAN JAZZ AND BEYOND, IGNACIO BERROA & HILARIO DURAN\r\nA series of clinics provides an historical view of the development of Afro-Cuban music, illuminating how the separate and distinct aspects of European and African contributions have combined to enrich the music world.', 'Details TBA', 124),
('TRACKING THINGS UNDER, ON AND OVER THE OCEAN: LESSONS LEARNED FROM 35 YEARS OF TRYING', 'Lectures, Seminars', 'Thursday April 9, 2015 - 11:30 AM', '2015-04-09', 'Abstract: \r\nHumans have always had the ability to track things. We use our our senses to make sure we know what we need to be aware of as we move through our environment. We use this information to make sure we do not run into things (navigation), to learn about things we would like to capture or study (surveillance) and to help us know who or what we would like to socialize with (communication). Over the past 100 years, Communication, Navigation and Surveillance (CNS) technologies have improved radically with exponentially growing geospatial coverage. This is especially true over the past 35 years, the span of the authors career at Defence R&D Canada. The purpose of this talk is to provide a retrospective look at the evolution of CNS technologies as they have been used in underwater surveillance, surface vessel navigation and aircraft monitoring (with a quick foray into cyberspace.) A goal of the talk is to help identify CNS technologies and concepts that might be of interest to th! ose who want to observe and monitor other types of activity in the ocean environment beyond military tracking applications. In particular, there appears to be growing interest in tracking ï¬sh and marine mammals in oceans, lakes and rivers around the world as well as monitoring activity around marine infrastructure such as oil drilling rigs, tidal and wind turbines and underwater communication and power cables. ', 'Slonim Conference Room (#430), Goldberg Computer Science Building', 125),
('PUBLIC LECTURE: MISSING MICROBES AND MODERN PLAGUES, BY MARTIN J. BLASER, M.D.', 'Lectures, Seminars', 'Thursday April 9, 2015 - 07:00 PM', '2015-04-09', 'A free public lecture by Martin J. Blaser, M.D., author of MISSING MICROBES. HOW THE OVERUSE OF ANTIBIOTICS IS FUELING OUR MODERN PLAGUES. Books will be available for purchase at the lecture.', 'Theatre B, Tupper Medical Building Link, 5850 College Street', 126),
('ARE YOU MANAGING YOUR MONEY, OR IS YOUR MONEY MANAGING YOU?', 'Training & Professional Development', 'Friday April 10, 2015 - 12:00 PM', '2015-04-10', 'Ever wonder where all your money goes? Are you feeling stretched at times to make ends meet? Do you get to the end of the money before you get to the end of the month?\r\n\r\nLet''s talk about your money and find ways to cut those costs, get on top of your debt instead of being buried by it, and get you feeling good about your relationship with your money. ', 'Room B400, lower level, Killam Library', 127),
('NEW MUSIC INITIATIVES RECITAL', 'Concerts, Performances & Arts', 'Friday April 10, 2015 - 12:00 PM', '2015-04-10', 'Students of Jérôme Blais', 'Sculpture Court, Dalhousie Arts Centre', 128),
('PHD DEFENCE - DEPARTMENT OF CHEMISTRY', 'Lectures, Seminars', 'Monday April 13, 2015 - 01:30 PM', '2015-04-13', 'The Faculty of Graduate Studies wishes to announce John Camadese, PhD candidate from the Department of Chemistry, will be defending his thesis entitled Core-Shell Materials as Positive Electrodes in Lithium-Ion Batteries on Monday, April 13, 2015, at 1:30pm.', 'Room 3107, The Mona Campbell Building, 1459 LeMarchant Street', 129),
('HOMOLOGOUS SERIES IN SOLID STATE CHEMISTRY: STACKING SLABS IN RARE-EARTH ARSENIDES', 'Lectures, Seminars', 'Tuesday April 14, 2015 - 11:00 AM', '2015-04-14', 'Professor Arthur Mar \r\nDepartment of Chemistry \r\nUniversity of Alberta \r\nhttp://xray.chem.ualberta.ca/mar/bio.htm ', 'Chemistry Room 226', 130),
('BIOCHEMISTRY & MOLECULAR BIOLOGY SEMINAR', 'Lectures, Seminars', 'Wednesday April 15, 2015 - 04:00 PM', '2015-04-15', 'Matthew Harty, M.Sc. Candidate \r\nCharacterizing the Entatic State of the Cambialistic Enzyme Mandelate Racemase\r\n\r\nSergio Munoz, M.Sc. Candidate \r\nThe Origin and Early Evolution of Mitochondrial Structure', 'Theatre A, Sir Charles Tupper Medical Building (Halifax) Room 102, DMNB (Saint John)', 131),
('FILM SCREENING: M', 'Movies & Film', 'Wednesday April 15, 2015 - 08:00 PM', '2015-04-15', 'M \r\nJoseph Losey, USA, 1951, 88 minutes. Soon to be blacklisted, Joseph Losey remade Fritz Lang’s famous 1931 child-murderer classic in Los Angeles, updating the story with surprising verve and panache', 'Dalhousie Art Gallery\r\n', 132),
('3 MINUTE THESIS - FINAL ROUND', 'Special Events', 'April 16, 2015 - 07:00 PM - 08:00 PM', '2015-04-16', 'The Faculty of Graduate Studies (FGS) is excited to announce the third annual Three Minute Thesis (3MT) competition at Dalhousie University. Preliminary heats will take place on Thursday April 9th, and the final will be held on the evening of Thursday April 16th 2015. The competitions are open to the public, and faculty and staff are encouraged to support the competition both by encouraging students to compete and by coming out to watch the participants on Thursday April 9th, and Thursday April 16th. We would also like to invite faculty to bring classes to watch the heats on April 9th.', 'Room 1016, Rowe Building, 6100 University Avenue', 133),
('WHALES AND HUMANS: A COMPLEX RELATIONSHIP', 'Lectures, Seminars', 'April 20, 2015 - 07:00 PM - 08:30 PM', '2015-04-20', 'A talk by Armando Manolo Alvarez Torres of the Department of Biology of Dalhousie University on the philosophies and perceptions behind conservation approaches.', 'Rowe Building, Room 1014', 134),
('BIOCHEMISTRY & MOLECULAR BIOLOGY SEMINAR - DR. DENIS DUPRE', 'Lectures, Seminars', 'Wednesday April 22, 2015 - 04:00 PM', '2015-04-22', 'Dr. Denis Dupre, Associate Professor \r\nDepartment of Pharmacology \r\nSenior Scientist, Beatrice Hunter Cancer Research Institute \r\nDalhousie University \r\n\r\nUnderstanding G-protein Coupled Receptor Function and Specificity Through Analysis of Their Role in Cancer and Oligomerization', 'Theatre A, Sir Charles Tupper Medical Building Link (Halifax), Room 102, DMNB (Saint John)', 135),
('FILM SCREENING: THE BIGAMIST', 'Movies & Film', 'Wednesday April 22, 2015 - 08:00 PM', '2015-04-22', 'The Bigamist \r\nIda Lupino, USA, 1953, 80 minutes. Actress and filmmaker Ida Lupino is the only woman to helm a Film Noir. Here she directs herself as one of two women married to the same man in this socially conscious story of marital betrayal that blends neo-realism with Noir.', 'Dalhousie Art Gallery', 136),
('BIOCHEMISTRY & MOLECULAR BIOLOGY - DR. MONTSE SANCHEZ-CESPEDES', 'Lectures, Seminars', 'Thursday April 23, 2015 - 04:00 PM', '2015-04-23', 'Dr. Montse Sanchez-Cespedes, Group Leader \r\nCancer Epigenetics & Biology Program \r\nBellvitge Biomedical Research Institute \r\nHospital Durant I Reynals Av. Gran Via de Hospitalet \r\nBarcelona, Spain ', 'Theatre C, Sir Charles Tupper Medical Building Link (Halifax) Room 218, DMNB (Saint John)', 137),
('CGEB SEMINAR', 'Lectures, Seminars', 'Starts: Thursday April 2, 2015 - 09:30 A', '2015-04-02', 'Dr. Bernard Lemire \r\nProfessor, Department of Biochemistry \r\nUniversity of Alberta \r\n\r\nGlutathione metabolism links FOXRED1 to NADH: Ubiquinone oxidoreductase (complex I) deficiency: A hypothesis', 'Theatre D, Clinical Research Centre', 138),
('UNDERSTANDING PAIN', 'Health and Wellness', 'April 2, 2015 - 12:05 PM', '2015-04-02', 'Pain is essential for survival. It is an alarm system that warns us of potential danger. There are various medical causes for pain such as fractures and infections. There are various mechanical causes of pain that are addressed by a physiotherapist. These include pain caused by muscle weakness, muscle tightness, joint stiffness, acute injury of ligaments and tendons, irritated nerves and pain following prolonged postures. We will help you understand the factors that contribute to acute and chronic pain conditions and provide pain management recommendations', 'TBD', 139),
('WE INTERVIEW TECH', 'Special Events', 'Thursday April 2, 2015 - 06:30 PM - 8:30', '2015-04-02', 'The Dalhousie Women in Technology Society would like to formally invite you to We Interview Tech, our largest event of the semester! We Interview Tech will center around a panel of speakers answering questions on how to stand out when you are trying to get into the technology industry. This event will be a great opportunity to learn and network, and is free to all students, academia, and industry. We hope to see you for a great evening of networking, inspiration, and learning!\r\n\r\nRSVP: http://wetalktech.eventbrite.ca/\r\nFacebook Event: goo.gl/TWTxvX\r\n\r\nRefreshments will be served, and there are prizes to be won!', 'Student Union Buidling, Room 303', 140),
('FOUNTAIN SCHOOL OF PERFORMING ARTS STAGE PRODUCTION: THE SEAGULL', 'Concerts, Performances & Arts', 'March 31, 2015 - 08:00 PM  April 2, 2015', '2015-04-02', 'By Anton Chekhov \r\nIn a version by Martin Crimp \r\nDirected by Tanja Jacobs \r\nSir James Dunn Theatre ', 'Sir James Dunn Theatre, Dalhousie Arts Centre, 6101 University Avenue', 141),
